    <td  bgcolor="#FFFFFF" valign="TOP"><table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" border="0">
      <tr align="left">
        <td  bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="100%" valign="top"><font color="#08599C">
         <b>Author:&nbsp;<a class=doctorLink href="mailto:&#108;&#111;&#118;&#101;&#117;&#98;&#97;&#98;&#101;&#48;&#48;&#55;&#105;&#110;&#64;&#121;&#97;&#104;&#111;&#111;&#46;&#99;&#111;&#109;?subject=Opinion About Marat Safin By Other Big Names">Abhi</a> </b><br>
         <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
           <tr>
             <td><font color="#08599C"><b>Date:&nbsp;</b></font></td>
             <td><DIV DIR="ltr"><font color="#08599C"><b>19-10-2005 16:38</b></font></DIV></td>
           </tr>
         </table>
         <br>
      "Mats Wilander(SWE)"<br />
<br />
About Marat Safin, first of all I am not happy with the way he has been in and out. He goes in and actually believes that he is going to win. He might sometimes be a little crazy. He actually believes that he is a better player than Federer. You know what, he most probably is, when he plays well. When he doesn't play well he is not going to beat him. But he has the highest game. When he plays well, Roger Federer will not be able to beat him.<br />
<br />
With Safin, when the mind is there he plays well, and obviously if it is not there, he is not there.<br />
------------------------------------------------<br />
"Richard Krajicek"<br />
<br />
QUESTION:-Among all the younger players, who do you think is most capable of challenging Federer at his best?<br />
<br />
ANSWER:-I think they all have their own weapons. When Federer is playing at his best he is a very difficult player to beat. But if you look at Marat Safin and the way he can play from the back of the court, he is very talented as well. So, I think he can match up to him.<br />
----------------------------------------------<br />
"PETE SAMPRAS"<br />
<br />
Q:What are your thoughts on Roger Federer?<br />
<br />
PETE:"He's head and shoulders above everyone else.He's got a great game ,great attitude.He's all about winning and letting his Racket do the talking."<br />
<br />
Q:Can anyone Touch Him?<br />
<br />
PETE:"I don't see anyone challenging him.Marat Safin - He's got the game .When he's ON,he can hold his own against Roger Federer.but Mentally he's years behind.Hewitt,Roddick-They're not good enough<br />
-----------------------------------------------<br />
"PAT CASH"<br />
Marat Safin is brilliant but he is inconsistent<br />
------------------------------------------------<br />
"According To Me"<br />
<br />
Marat Safin the talented Big Russian with Serve among the best but here lies the difference between him and Roddick,His game is not based only on his serve but his all round game.Tremendous balance, good mobility fast reach and quick reflex makes him a naturally dangerous player.Like Roger he has loads of weapons but his mental inconsistency sometimes acts as a barrior for effective use of those weapons.His jumping backhand not only classy and a treat to watch but effective to maximum extent ,among best of all time.Technical error probably Null but the only problem inconsistency and his temper(Quite balanced and composed with the help of Roger's Ex Coach),If he can play with calm,composed and poised attitude ,He can be the most dangerous player of all because his potential was never doubted by anyone.Unpredictable ,Can win a grandslam and as well as face an early round exit.hard and risky to bet on but certainly tournaments are incomplete without his presence and undoubtly Roger's favourite opponent.<br />
</font></tt><p>
    </td>
